Firefighters in California, Michigan, Montana, Wyoming and Utah
battled holiday weekend fires that blackened more than 6,000 acres of
forest and wilderness areas.

Illegal fireworks were blamed for a blaze that swept over 2,200 acres
of Stanislaus National Forest in California.

In southern Utah's scenic Zion National Park, firefighters tried to
contain a 600-acre fire that was ignited by lightening.

Meanwhile, three-quarters of an inch of rain on Monday helped slow a
fire on 1,650 acres in the Shoshone National Forest in Wyoming.

A fire which burned 8,700 acres in Arizona's Tonto National Forest was
reported extinguished on Monday.</SUM>

